ProtoDefines:
. "Let $E$ and $F$ be two events. We say that they are 
   {independent\/} if either 1) both events have positive 
   probability and $$ P(E|F) = P(E)\ { and}\ P(F|E) = P(F)\ , 
   $$ or 2) at least one of the events has probability 0."
